ional | expert in luxury hotel management | ", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/last_name": "Haimoud", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/premium": "false", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/public_identifier": "sara-haimoud-9918ab373", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAAFyAyb0BGw9jnUoinzLBJrCFcFFKeU4L8CI", "profilePic": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D5603AQEHPLSDC4xG6w/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/B56ZQnHY0DG8Ac-/0/1735823037302?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=w02tMBW7fJVjrvzMViurSufuECm5sArk2KpesaYp1f8", "profilePicHighQuality": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D5603AQEHPLSDC4xG6w/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/B56ZQnHY0DG8Ac-/0/1735823037302?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=w02tMBW7fJVjrvzMViurSufuECm5sArk2KpesaYp1f8", "publicIdentifier": "ek-w-b70b7a8", "recommendations/0/context": "Ek worked with Bruno but on different teams", "recommendations/0/date": "February 24, 2012", "recommendations/0/description": "I had the pleasure of knowing and interacting with Bruno for about 4 years.  I found Bruno to be very professional and to the point in all business dealing.  He is very focused and driven.  He left no stone unturned before he arrived to his decision.  I also had a chance to speak with his colleague when Bruno sent him to stay with us, and his colleague spoke very highly of Bruno as a manager.  Bruno is a great manager.", "recommendations/0/name": "Bruno De Schuyter", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "General Manager at SCHLOSS Roxburghe, part of Destination by Hyatt", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/brunodeschuyter/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAHUzlkBZID1ju00Cwwxsj1EaYS4g85Zih0", "recommendations/1/context": "Ek was senior to Adam but didn't manage Adam directly", "recommendations/1/date": "August 19, 2009", "recommendations/1/description": "My name is Ek Wongleecharoen.  I am the Assistant General Manager at the \nRoger Smith Hotel.  I have worked with Adam Wallace since he graduated from Skidmore College in 2006.\n\nI am writing this letter in order to record my strong recommendation for Mr. Adam Wallace.\n\nMy support is firmly based on Adam’s exceptional ability and accomplishments in the area of public relation, media management, and web related areas which are so important to our organization.  He helps increase revenue by monitor and improving all these channels carefully with innovative approach.  He is a hard working gentleman.  His talents and qualifications are clearly transferable to a multitude of similar business.", "recommendations/1/name": "Adam Wallace", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "Founder & CEO of Spherical: The Agency for Inspired Hotels", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/adamjwallace/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAJtNhMBAaSZpZAIB_o7MFKsoDlEtgbzWY4", "recommendationsReceived/0/context": "Ek was senior to Carl but didn't manage Carl directly", "recommendationsReceived/0/date": "June 14, 2012", "recommendationsReceived/0/description": "During my year of management traineeship at the Roger Smith Hotel I had the pleasure of working together with Ek. \nHe showed great enthusiasm to share his hotel knowledge and was not only a great colleague but a also a good friend. \nEk was, and continues to be a great asset to the continous sucess of the Roger Smith Hotel.", "recommendationsReceived/0/name": "Carl Noresson", "recommendationsReceived/0/subtitle": "Market Manager på Expedia Group", "recommendationsReceived/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/carl-noresson-56a058a/", "recommendationsReceived/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAHJbiIBz5zJhSpyEQ9omU7c36QDoQryiBs", "recommendationsReceived/1/date": "February 10, 2012", "recommendationsReceived/1/description": "I had a pleasure of meeting EK during the General Manager Program at the Cornell University and I was very impressed with his social skills and his knowledge about the industry. I have relied on Ek's services and industry connections in NYC on several occasions and he continues to provide a great service to me and our clients. He is very talented and an excellent ambassador to the NYC’s hotel community.", "recommendationsReceived/1/name": "Klaudio Simic", "recommendationsReceived/1/subtitle": "President at Practice Hospitality", "recommendationsReceived/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/klaudio-simic-463b7b8/", "recommendationsReceived/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAGYx8sBh8oqO5Vwg82eahEJggJVYZ17Fss", "recommendationsReceived/2/context": "Ek was senior to Adam but didn't manage Adam directly", "recommendationsReceived/2/date": "February 1, 2012", "recommendationsReceived/2/description": "I had the pleasure of working with EK for more than 4 years and he was consistantly impressive in both his focus and attention to detail and his versatility, being able to take on just about any project that is given to him.  Ek is great with numbers and a creative problems solver. He carries himself very professionally but also has a good sense of humor, making him a great person to work with.", "recommendationsReceived/2/name": "Adam Wallace", "recommendationsReceived/2/subtitle": "Founder & CEO of Spherical: The Agency for Inspired Hotels", "recommendationsReceived/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/adamjwallace/", "recommendationsReceived/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAJtNhMBAaSZpZAIB_o7MFKsoDlEtgbzWY4", "recommendationsReceived/3/context": "Simon worked with Ek but they were at different companies", "recommendationsReceived/3/date": "January 30, 2012", "recommendationsReceived/3/description": "I met Ek during Worldhotels Executive Meeting. He was great.", "recommendationsReceived/3/name": "Simon Sin", "recommendationsReceived/3/subtitle": "Owner, Cova Hotel", "recommendationsReceived/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/simon-sin-2644346/", "recommendationsReceived/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAEhn2wBX-JG7Y03IUIodOs4R6RI4yVFSF4", "recommendationsReceived/4/context": "Jean - 'JK' - worked with Ek but they were at different companies", "recommendationsReceived/4/date": "January 29, 2012", "recommendationsReceived/4/description": "Ek and I have been engaged over the years, post our initial meet up at Cornell. \nAt those engagements, Ek has always been able to 'catch my attention' almost instantly as he is 'that kind of personality'. An outgoing and pleasing character is the basis for this.\nHaving had the pleasure to reside at the Roger Smith's Hotel in NY, you will quickly recognize the easy going -but at all times: professional- casual atmosphere amongst the team members. Something which I associate and expect from those who 'hang and work around' with Ek.\nHenceforth, it is obvious that I feel strongly about writing a recommendation to his benefit. As and when more insights are required, feel free to call in with me.\nJK", "recommendationsReceived/4/name": "Jean - 'JK' - Keijdener, CHA, FIH, CFBE, CLM, CM, CHIA", "recommendationsReceived/4/subtitle": "Making people successful at McCalls Catering & Events", "recommendationsReceived/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/jeankeijdener/", "recommendationsReceived/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAABovZUBlASxqrNgK4344Jzkm-9TnlssNh0", "recommendationsReceived/5/context": "Ek was Gerard's client", "recommendationsReceived/5/date": "January 25, 2012", "recommendationsReceived/5/description": "Its been a pleasure to know Ek whom I met at the General Manager's Program at Cornell.\n\nHe is an infectiously enthusiastic individual with a great zest for life and the hospitality business.\n\nHe has great leadership qualities and has proved to be a great networker and communicator . His advanced technological skills have helped all us who attended GMP Cornell to stay in touch .\n\nIt is a pleasure to know Ek  , he is a great ambassador for the hospitality business.", "recommendationsReceived/5/name": "Gerard Denneny", "recommendationsReceived/5/subtitle": "Hospitality Consultant Ireland | Hotel management | Customer Service Operations | HR Policy and Practise | HR 